criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        (1) Adult patients with SBS, defined as intestinal malabsorption disorder resulting from
        extensive bowel resection with a remnant small intestine length of greater than 200 cm,
        admitted to a clinical nutrition center.

        -

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. age less than 18 years;

          2. previous history of thyroidal, hypophyseal or hypothalamic disease;

          3. lactational or gestational period;

          4. medication history of thyroidal hormone or antithyroid drugs;

          5. craniocerebral injury;

          6. attack of coronary heart disease, myocardial, or cerebral infarction in the past
             month;

          7. intracranial infection or hemorrhage in the past month. -
